The Kwara State Chapter of the Peoples Democratic Party (PDP) on Monday in Ilorin inaugurated an 18-man Reconciliation and Engagement Committee to reconcile aggrieved members of the party. Former Acting National Chairman of the PDP, Alhaji Abubakar Kawu Baraje, who chaired the committee, called on members to work assiduously towards achieving the desired result and assured the leadership of the party that they would do a thorough job and deliver on their terms of reference. Baraje, who acknowledged the enormous task before the committee members, called for sacrifice and selflessness to make the committee a reference point and return it to power in 2023. 